<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="1603" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1603">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/108.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Vice-Consul <persName type="from">Blocker</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eagle Pass</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 31, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I have refused to certify invoices of coal entered for export to the
                                United States by Constitutionalists authorities because coal was
                                taken from Rio Esconclido and Agujita coal mines owned by French and
                                American citizens. The mines were confiscated by Constitutionalists
                                on May 19, 1914. Out of 20,000 shares Rio Escondido, French and
                                American citizens hold more than eighty per cent of stock.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Blocker.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>